comments: The contact between VanVleet (TOR) and Holiday (IND) is marginal.  Holiday raises his off-arm at the point of contact, but the level of contact is not consistent with his reaction.
Turner (IND) sets the pick in VanVleet's (TOR) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
VanVleet (TOR) makes marginal contact with Holiday's (IND) non-shooting arm during his shooting motion that does not affect the driving shot attempt.
Hollis-Jefferson (TOR) makes marginal contact with Lamb (IND) as he disengages from the pick.
Lamb (IND) makes marginal contact with Lowry's (TOR) body during the driving shot attempt.
Ibaka (TOR) is in the paint for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Sabonis (IND) makes incidental contact with Lowry's (TOR) body at the end of the drive.
Holiday (IND) and Ibaka (TOR) engage and separate during the rebound.
Anunoby (TOR) sets the pick in Lamb's (IND) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Warren (IND) makes marginal contact with Lowry's (TOR) arm during his drive that does not prevent Lowry from gathering the ball.
Lowry (TOR) leans into Warren (IND) during his shooting motion but the contact is marginal on the driving shot attempt.
During the pick, VanVleet (TOR) holds Turner (IND) and affects his FOM.
Ibaka (TOR) makes marginal contact with Holiday's (IND) body during his shooting motion on the driving shot attempt.
Sabonis (IND) has his arm extended but he does not dislodge Hollis-Jefferson (TOR) from his rebounding position, as Hollis-Jefferson is already jumping in the direction he lands.
VanVleet (TOR) makes incidental contact with Sabonis (IND) after Sabonis loses control of the ball.
Lamb (IND) legally contests Lowry's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
Lowry (TOR) releases from contact with Turner (IND) and does not dislodge him from his defensive position.
Lamb (IND) makes contact to Hollis-Jefferson's (TOR) wrist that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Ibaka (TOR) splits his feet.
Ibaka (TOR) extends his arm into Lamb (IND) and dislodges him at the start of the drive.
Lowry (TOR) and Turner (IND) make incidental contact during rebounding.
Sabonis (IND) makes more than marginal contact with Hollis-Jefferson's (TOR) head during the rebound.
VanVleet (TOR) makes marginal contact with Lamb's (IND) front as Lamb loses control of his dribble.
Lowry (TOR) makes marginal contact with Lamb's (IND) body at the end of the drive.
Sabonis (IND) is firming up in a picking position in Lowry's (TOR) path when contact occurs and he absorbs the contact.
Lowry (TOR) braces his forearm and makes marginal contact with Warren (IND) at the end of the drive.
Anunoby (TOR) sets the pick in Lamb's (IND) path and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Turner (IND) and Ibaka (TOR) make incidental contact during the loose ball situation.
Ibaka (TOR) makes contact with the ball before making incidental contact with Warren (IND) as he goes to the floor.
Holiday (IND) establishes himself in the frontcourt before eight seconds has elapsed.
VanVleet (TOR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Holiday (IND) in the backcourt.
Hollis-Jefferson (TOR) cleanly blocks Holiday's (IND) jump shot attempt before making incidental high five contact with his hand.
Turner's (IND) arm is extended when he makes contact with Lowry (TOR) as the shot clock is expiring.  He does not push him during the loose ball.
Correctly called 24 second shot clock violation.
Ibaka (TOR) moves laterally as he screens Lamb (IND), and Ibaka is in a wide position when lower leg contact occurs.
Hollis-Jefferson (TOR) holds Warren's (IND) arm and affects his SQBR.
Anunoby (TOR) commits a take foul on Sabonis (IND).
Holiday (IND) legally contests VanVleet's (TOR) jump shot attempt.
